observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the City Mayor direct:

The City Accountant to – 

Require the persons in-charge of recording the PPE in the SL, and preparing the LS, to coordinate, communicate and collaborate with each other to reconcile their records;

Reconcile the accounting records with the OGS RPCPPE to address the noted deficiencies;

The Officer-in-Charge (OIC)-OGS to obtain the TCTs of all City-owned parcels of land to establish absolute ownership and mitigate possible legal risks; and 

The CAO and OGS to facilitate the review, verification, and reconciliation of all PPE accounts, and to follow strictly the procedures prescribed in COA Circular No. 2020-006 for the one-time cleansing of the PPE balances.

We recommended that the City Mayor address the deficiencies by directing:

The City Assessor to implement a standardized PIN pursuant to the MRPAAO issued by the BLGF in CAO and CTO records/reports; undertake corrective measures to prevent identical PIN in the AR; rectify and adjust accordingly the assessment of properties with MV that are not in conformity and/or aligned with the specified SMV prescribed by City Ordinance No. 6; and to execute the necessary updating in the AR of all real properties within the jurisdiction of the City to enable the CTO to give complete reports to the CAO for a more accurate and reliable balances of the RPT and SET Receivable accounts as of year-end;

The City Treasurer to include the 3,200 properties in the set-up of RPT and SET receivables and to refund the taxes collected to previous property owner, now owned by the City;

The City Assessor and City Treasurer to conduct a thorough/complete reconciliation of the Certified List of Receivables and the AR to identify and correct the inconsistencies in the property listings and assessed values; and

The Head-MISO to make the necessary adjustments in the computerized system.

