observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Management instruct the CAO to:
Properly reconcile their accounting records (GF and SEF) to correct/eliminate the discrepancies as identified;
Conduct a comprehensive review of the calculation of depreciation of PPE;
Ensure that the residual value as prescribed is properly applied and not reinstated in the computation of depreciation; and
Effect the necessary adjustments so that the depreciation of the PPE strictly complies with PAG 6, Paragraph 88 of IPSAS 17.

We recommended that the Management instruct:
The Head of CHD, Medical Director of PCGH, and Medical Director of PCCH to –
Regularly reconcile the records of the City’s HFs and HCIs pertaining to benefit claims with the records of PhilHealth to ensure that AP of PhilHealth is reconciled with AR of HFs and HCIs;
Enhance collection for RTH and Denied claims to PhilHealth by strictly monitoring the same to increase funds for health-related PPAs; and
Submit to CAO the –
Outstanding receivables as of December 31, 2024, from patients who do not qualify under the No Balance Billing Policy of the City for recording of receivables and adjustment to Government Equity account;
Outstanding claims from PhilHealth as of December 31, 2024 for recording in Due from GOCCs account, Other Payables account and adjustment to Government Equity account;
List of RTH and Denied Claims as of December 31, 2024 for monitoring and proper recording in the books;
List of re-filed RTH claims and Appealed Claims as of December 31, 2024;
Records of gross and net billings of patients served by the City’s HFs and HCIs for accrual of income and recording of receivables on a monthly basis;
Claims for reimbursements filed to PhilHealth for accrual of income and recording of receivables and other payables on a monthly basis; and
Notification Letter from PhilHealth for RTH and Denied Claims.
The CAO to –
Reclassify previously recorded Other Payables to Barangay Health Centers to Government Equity to avoid non-recognition of income and expenses pertaining to receipt and utilization of PhilHealth share by Barangay Health Centers;
Record the outstanding receivables from patients and PhilHealth as of December 31, 2024, based on the records that will be submitted by the CHD, PCGH and PCCH;
Ensure the proper recognition of income and receivables, both from paying patients and claims from PhilHealth, for services rendered by City’s HFs and HCIs based on the monthly reports to be submitted by the CHD, PCGH and PCCH;
Ensure that RTH and Denied Claims are deducted from Due from GOCCs account based on the Notification Letter issued by PhilHealth; and
Regularly reconcile its records with CHD, PCGH and PCCH to ensure that correct/proper amounts is recorded in the books of account of the City.

We recommended that the City Mayor direct:

The City Accountant to include all the expenditures charged to the LDRRMF in the RUD of DRRMF;

The Head-CPDO to strictly monitor the implementation of the City’s priority PPAs;

The Head-CDRRMO to coordinate with the Head-CPDO and City Accountant to effectively monitor the implementation and utilization of the targeted PPAs and to prepare the complete RUD, respectively; and

The Chairperson-BAC to expedite the procurement process to ensure the timely implementation of the planned PPAs and to avoid under-utilization of the LDRRMF.

